Senegal's national team took time to have some fun on the pitch as they trained - which has caught the attention of social media. JOHANNESBURG - When they're not flying their country's flag high and making Africa proud at the 2018 Fifa World Cup, Senegal's national team takes time to have some fun on the pitch as they train - which has caught the attention of social media. Prior to their meeting with Japan on Sun, day which saw both sides ending on a 2 -2 draw, the Senegalese team was spotted having a good time as they dance-trained on the pitch. The video has been posted on Twitter and already has over 30,000 retweets and close four million views. 